1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:04,773 --> 00:00:05,952
<i>[Episode 13]</i>

3
00:00:05,952 --> 00:00:07,833
Seriously, it came out again.

4
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:11,236
See, you threw out this hair clip
for no reason and it's all bent now!

5
00:00:13,048 --> 00:00:14,755
Seriously...

6
00:00:14,755 --> 00:00:16,227
Hand it over.

7
00:00:19,075 --> 00:00:20,657
Come over here.

8
00:00:27,810 --> 00:00:29,245
Did it work?

9
00:00:42,290 --> 00:00:46,655
But... about that story of the Little
Mermaid you mentioned yesterday.

10
00:00:46,655 --> 00:00:48,565
Does it really end like that?

11
00:00:49,676 --> 00:00:54,066
To my knowledge, the Little Mermaid
doesn't disappear into sea foam bubbles.

12
00:00:58,092 --> 00:01:00,444
The Prince can't remember,
so what can you do?

13
00:01:06,454 --> 00:01:08,567
How would you have
liked it to end then?

14
00:01:10,522 --> 00:01:11,804
Me?

15
00:01:30,485 --> 00:01:32,651
Hey, hurry up!
The boat came in!

16
00:01:38,445 --> 00:01:41,143
People must be waiting. Let's go.

17
00:01:55,498 --> 00:01:57,452
About that Little Mermaid
story earlier...

18
00:01:59,853 --> 00:02:01,507
I remembered how it ended.

19
00:02:03,137 --> 00:02:05,562
How... does it end?

20
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:18,767
'The moment the Little Mermaid
turns into sea foam bubbles...'

21
00:02:22,043 --> 00:02:25,671
'The Prince's memory...'

22
00:02:25,671 --> 00:02:27,590
returned.'

23
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,789
Shouldn't fairytales
usually end like that?

24
00:02:45,789 --> 00:02:47,218
A happy ending.

25
00:02:47,218 --> 00:02:49,557
People don't know fairytales very well.

26
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:55,931
Soo In, when did you get here?

27
00:02:55,931 --> 00:02:58,163
- Just now.
- Let's go.

28
00:03:12,105 --> 00:03:13,795
Are you all right?

29
00:03:16,743 --> 00:03:18,687
Yes.

30
00:03:18,687 --> 00:03:21,447
I'm sorry to have made
you worry over nothing.

31
00:03:23,121 --> 00:03:25,069
Not at all. Let's go.

32
00:03:37,222 --> 00:03:39,799
That's right. It isn't over yet.

33
00:03:40,251 --> 00:03:43,324
Snap out of it, Park Soo In.

34
00:03:49,086 --> 00:03:51,120
- This way.
- Yes.

35
00:03:54,296 --> 00:03:58,107
President Jo!
Let's have dinner together.

36
00:03:58,107 --> 00:04:00,192
I have something to
tell you as well.

37
00:04:25,604 --> 00:04:27,524
Let's eat.

38
00:04:28,292 --> 00:04:32,131
- Did you find what you lost?
- Yes, I did.

39
00:04:32,845 --> 00:04:35,102
What was it that you
were in such a hurry?

40
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:38,739
This is all because of that
hair clip you bought her.

41
00:04:39,963 --> 00:04:43,266
Spend money if you're going
to buy a present for your girlfriend.

42
00:04:43,266 --> 00:04:44,645
How countrified.

43
00:04:50,617 --> 00:04:52,447
Go on, eat.

44
00:04:58,474 --> 00:04:59,979
What?

45
00:04:59,979 --> 00:05:02,393
Is it the first time you've seen
someone wrap eel in lettuce?

46
00:05:03,509 --> 00:05:05,278
It's delicious wrapped
in sesame leaf as well.

47
00:05:05,278 --> 00:05:08,662
President Jo. I told you that
I had something to tell you.

48
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:13,138
Joon Hyun and I are getting engaged.

49
00:05:15,372 --> 00:05:17,744
I felt like you should know
ahead of time.

50
00:05:19,023 --> 00:05:23,240
We're planning a quiet occasion
without letting the press know.

51
00:05:24,673 --> 00:05:27,242
Yes well... that's
something to celebrate.

52
00:05:27,242 --> 00:05:29,446
Congratulations.

53
00:05:37,835 --> 00:05:41,393
Did I... do something wrong
by bringing up the engagement party?

54
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:48,689
I'm sorry for deciding that
on my own without consulting you.

55
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:53,107
No, it's okay. Let's go.

56
00:06:07,927 --> 00:06:09,403
You're going to go home, right?

57
00:06:11,018 --> 00:06:13,871
No, I'll go to the practice studio.

58
00:06:15,328 --> 00:06:17,456
I'd like for you to rest at home today.

59
00:06:18,951 --> 00:06:22,441
I'm fine. Don't worry about me.

60
00:06:26,838 --> 00:06:28,796
You don't have to be like that
in front of me.

61
00:06:28,796 --> 00:06:30,613
Do whatever you want.

62
00:06:30,613 --> 00:06:32,468
Don't hold it in.

63
00:06:45,607 --> 00:06:49,044
<i>Joon Hyun and I are getting engaged.</i>

64
00:07:19,932 --> 00:07:23,538
Joon Hyun and I are getting engaged.

65
00:07:26,011 --> 00:07:27,867
Found it!

66
00:07:46,031 --> 00:07:49,351
We found this at the crime scene.
Is this yours?

67
00:07:56,113 --> 00:07:58,049
- Tae Song.
<i>- Where are you right now?</i>

68
00:07:59,127 --> 00:08:01,905
I'm on my way to hand my cellphone
to a repair shop...

69
00:08:02,938 --> 00:08:04,695
Never mind. I'll go myself.

70
00:08:06,699 --> 00:08:09,601
It'll take some time to recover
the videos.

71
00:08:09,601 --> 00:08:12,106
I'll contact you.

72
00:08:18,397 --> 00:08:20,166
He isn't here.

73
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:42,357
[Happy Call Electronics]

74
00:08:44,355 --> 00:08:47,321
<i>Customer, were you happy
with your service?</i>

75
00:08:47,321 --> 00:08:52,476
<i>We'll contact you when the phone
you gave us is repaired. Thank you.</i>

76
00:08:54,003 --> 00:08:55,515
He gave them a cellphone to repair?

77
00:08:55,515 --> 00:08:57,926
But this is his cellphone.

78
00:08:59,082 --> 00:09:01,640
No way...

79
00:09:06,959 --> 00:09:08,569
- You're here?
- You're here.

80
00:09:12,272 --> 00:09:14,194
These are the locations for
our engagement party.

81
00:09:14,194 --> 00:09:15,748
Why don't you choose.

82
00:09:15,748 --> 00:09:18,276
I think this one is run down
despite it being popular...

83
00:09:18,718 --> 00:09:21,286
What? He already picked it up?

84
00:09:21,286 --> 00:09:23,707
Jang Joon Hyun picked up
his cellphone in person.

85
00:09:26,803 --> 00:09:28,554
Are you all right?

86
00:09:33,891 --> 00:09:36,207
Why didn't I think of
that cellphone earlier?

87
00:09:36,692 --> 00:09:38,986
It's all over if he looks
at that cellphone!

88
00:09:38,986 --> 00:09:41,320
It'll have pictures of them
together and everything!

89
00:09:42,111 --> 00:09:44,719
What do we do now?
What are we going to do?

90
00:09:44,719 --> 00:09:46,833
Calm down.
Your engagement's coming up soon.

91
00:09:48,273 --> 00:09:49,728
I'll take care of the cellphone.

92
00:09:49,728 --> 00:09:51,575
You trust me, don't you?

93
00:09:58,109 --> 00:10:00,054
[Lee Hwa Soon: LA Address]

94
00:10:06,613 --> 00:10:08,797
Hello?

95
00:10:08,797 --> 00:10:11,371
Is this Hwa Soon?
It's me, Yang Joo Hee.

96
00:10:13,703 --> 00:10:15,748
Right, it's been a while.

97
00:10:15,748 --> 00:10:19,698
Did you hear? That Joon Hyun
and Soo In are getting engaged?

98
00:10:19,698 --> 00:10:22,489
Goodness, you didn't know?

99
00:10:23,656 --> 00:10:26,584
These are all the albums
Shine Star produced.

100
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:31,021
Should I call it a
kind of honorary hall?

101
00:10:31,695 --> 00:10:34,038
Wow.

102
00:10:34,038 --> 00:10:35,458
Choose one.

103
00:10:35,458 --> 00:10:39,730
See if there's a record that
could be your role model.

104
00:10:47,207 --> 00:10:49,687
What if you put out a ballad?

105
00:10:50,421 --> 00:10:51,452
What?

106
00:10:51,452 --> 00:10:53,659
There's no rule saying
you have to stick to trot.

107
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:57,039
Think about it.
There are a lot of options.

108
00:11:06,971 --> 00:11:08,356
Joon Hyun.

109
00:11:08,356 --> 00:11:10,317
Yes, Soo In.

110
00:11:11,264 --> 00:11:13,520
Our engagement party
invitations came today.

111
00:11:17,806 --> 00:11:20,860
Who would you invite from Shine Star?

112
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:23,316
I was going to ask my mom first.

113
00:11:27,149 --> 00:11:29,398
Choon Hee.

114
00:11:33,642 --> 00:11:37,920
Our engagement party is on Monday.
You can come, right?

115
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:42,661
We shouldn't do that.
How about you sing a celebratory song?

116
00:11:42,661 --> 00:11:47,195
We can quiet down the rumors
between the three of us that way.

117
00:11:47,195 --> 00:11:49,852
- Soo In.
- I have an event that day.

118
00:12:08,781 --> 00:12:10,951
I'm sorry.

119
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:14,324
About what?

120
00:12:14,337 --> 00:12:15,772
Asking you to sing
a celebratory song.

121
00:12:27,778 --> 00:12:29,714
Are you happy?

122
00:12:33,883 --> 00:12:36,810
What reason would I have...
not to be?

123
00:12:45,642 --> 00:12:48,477
That's enough then.

124
00:12:53,955 --> 00:12:56,371
I gave out all the invitations.

125
00:12:56,371 --> 00:12:58,738
I promised to give them
a call the day before...

126
00:12:58,738 --> 00:13:00,919
- Soo In?
- Yeah?

127
00:13:02,363 --> 00:13:05,206
Don't misunderstand what
I'm going to say and just listen.

128
00:13:07,038 --> 00:13:10,631
There's something I need to confirm...
before the engagement party.

129
00:13:10,631 --> 00:13:12,812
So about that...

130
00:13:12,812 --> 00:13:15,125
Couldn't we postpone
the engagement party?

131
00:13:15,856 --> 00:13:18,019
- Joon Hyun.
- No, it's that...

132
00:13:18,019 --> 00:13:20,936
- It's not because of something else...
- Is there another woman?

133
00:13:20,936 --> 00:13:22,440
Huh?

134
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,531
Tell me the truth.

135
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:27,082
It's not like that.

136
00:13:28,075 --> 00:13:30,170
That's enough then.

137
00:13:32,574 --> 00:13:38,191
Joon Hyun. After a sudden accident
and losing your memory...

138
00:13:38,191 --> 00:13:41,258
I understand that you're probably
really confused lately.

139
00:13:42,345 --> 00:13:45,402
Let's try a little harder, okay?

140
00:13:45,912 --> 00:13:49,169
And...

141
00:13:50,439 --> 00:13:52,206
Thanks.

142
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:57,614
You saved me at the concert hall.
I won't ever forget that.

143
00:13:57,614 --> 00:14:00,542
I wanted to make sure
that I told you these words.

144
00:14:17,359 --> 00:14:19,494
What's all this?

145
00:14:19,494 --> 00:14:21,127
Son!

146
00:14:21,127 --> 00:14:25,716
Oh, my son! Have you been well?

147
00:14:25,716 --> 00:14:28,234
Mom. Why did you come here?

148
00:14:28,234 --> 00:14:31,888
What do you mean? Should I not come
even if my son's getting engaged?

149
00:14:31,888 --> 00:14:36,467
Yang Joo... I mean,
Soo In's mother called me.

150
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:38,937
My impressive son.

151
00:14:41,295 --> 00:14:45,385
How long has it been, Hwa Soon?
You haven't changed.

152
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:48,790
I always look the same.
But you've seemed to age.

153
00:14:51,522 --> 00:14:54,004
- We're both getting older.
- 'We'?

154
00:14:54,004 --> 00:14:58,504
Oh dear, there are people asking me
if I'm in my twenties in the States.

155
00:15:00,432 --> 00:15:03,131
Mother, we're seeing each other
after quite a while.

156
00:15:03,131 --> 00:15:05,705
- Do you remember me?
- Oh yes, Soo In.

157
00:15:06,912 --> 00:15:09,092
It's the first time seeing each other
since you were young, right?

158
00:15:09,092 --> 00:15:13,377
- How pretty you've grown up to be.
- Thank you.

159
00:15:13,377 --> 00:15:15,602
But who's going to pay for the house?

160
00:15:17,275 --> 00:15:19,772
- House?
- The house the kids will live in.

161
00:15:19,772 --> 00:15:22,595
Shouldn't you have
prepared one if you're

162
00:15:22,608 --> 00:15:25,442
getting Joon Hyun
as a son-in-law?

163
00:15:35,515 --> 00:15:38,391
[Soo In]

164
00:15:51,021 --> 00:15:53,601
Are you happy?

165
00:16:03,228 --> 00:16:07,349
Jang Joon Hyun and Park Soo In
are getting engaged today.

166
00:16:07,349 --> 00:16:10,719
What? Jang Joon Hyun
and Park Soo In?

167
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:18,586
Per your instructions, I also
looked into Yang Joo Hee.

168
00:16:18,586 --> 00:16:20,422
Is that right?

169
00:16:42,853 --> 00:16:45,931
You have to go back to your owner now.

170
00:16:51,548 --> 00:16:56,445
Right. You at least have to stay
by Jang Joon Hyun's side.

171
00:16:58,394 --> 00:17:00,678
I'll miss you.

172
00:17:21,692 --> 00:17:23,176
It was here.

173
00:17:32,982 --> 00:17:36,553
<i>I'll make sure to find
your guitar for you. Choon Hee.</i>

174
00:17:49,953 --> 00:17:54,754
Goodness, President Jo.
What brings you?

175
00:17:55,304 --> 00:17:57,601
Were you responsible
for the scandal

176
00:17:57,614 --> 00:17:59,922
between Choi Choon Hee
and the politician?

177
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:02,618
Excuse me?

178
00:18:02,618 --> 00:18:04,697
Choi Choon Hee is a singer
I told you to train.

179
00:18:04,697 --> 00:18:07,391
But you fed her to the wolves
like that, Director Yang?

180
00:18:09,864 --> 00:18:12,251
What was your reason for that?

181
00:18:12,251 --> 00:18:15,930
I don't know what you're talking about.

182
00:18:15,930 --> 00:18:18,792
I don't know what
you've heard...

183
00:18:18,805 --> 00:18:21,678
Did you know Choon Hee
is Sung Joo's daughter?

184
00:18:22,465 --> 00:18:25,182
I have a debt to Oh Sung Joo.

185
00:18:25,737 --> 00:18:29,758
I'll take care of Choi Choon Hee
until her father returns.

186
00:18:29,758 --> 00:18:31,917
I'm warning you, Director Yang.

187
00:18:31,917 --> 00:18:36,269
If you mess with Choi Choon Hee
one more time...

188
00:18:37,437 --> 00:18:40,487
I won't stand for it.

189
00:18:50,381 --> 00:18:55,771
President Jo just came by.

190
00:18:55,771 --> 00:18:57,801
He claims to know everything
about Choi Choon Hee.

191
00:18:57,801 --> 00:18:59,661
It's okay.

192
00:18:59,661 --> 00:19:05,532
If this gets out, then let's take
care of Choi Choon Hee for good.

193
00:19:14,918 --> 00:19:18,436
Jang Joon Hyun?

194
00:19:21,608 --> 00:19:24,148
Someone asked me to deliver this to you.

195
00:19:26,103 --> 00:19:29,623
Who... dropped this off?

196
00:19:29,623 --> 00:19:32,834
A woman dropped by not too long ago
and asked me to give this to you.

197
00:19:32,834 --> 00:19:35,121
- A woman?
- Yes.

198
00:20:12,234 --> 00:20:13,900
Choi Choon Hee?

199
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:18,266
Choi Choon Hee!

200
00:20:34,981 --> 00:20:38,117
Choi Choon Hee!

201
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,658
Choi Choon Hee!

202
00:20:48,103 --> 00:20:50,039
Choi Choon Hee!

203
00:20:52,794 --> 00:20:54,794
Choi Choon Hee!

204
00:20:57,898 --> 00:21:02,174
Choi Choon Hee!

205
00:21:27,474 --> 00:21:29,529
Are you awake now?

206
00:21:33,368 --> 00:21:34,846
Choi Choon Hee.

207
00:21:34,846 --> 00:21:36,742
What about Choi Choon Hee?

208
00:21:40,702 --> 00:21:43,456
She's asleep.
She'll wake up soon.

209
00:21:47,386 --> 00:21:50,210
She'll be fine once she's stabilized.

210
00:21:50,210 --> 00:21:52,444
Neither of you have to worry.

211
00:22:16,764 --> 00:22:22,168
<i>I want to say that I love you</i>

212
00:22:22,168 --> 00:22:28,490
<i>Just riding on this wish</i>

213
00:22:28,490 --> 00:22:31,365
<i>Afraid that you might leave</i>

214
00:22:31,365 --> 00:22:31,487
- Choi Choon Hee.
- Hmm?
<i>Afraid that you might leave</i>

215
00:22:31,487 --> 00:22:33,479
- Choi Choon Hee.
- Hmm?

216
00:22:33,479 --> 00:22:36,038
Sorry.

217
00:22:55,927 --> 00:22:57,942
Are you okay?

218
00:22:58,669 --> 00:23:00,769
Huh?

219
00:23:01,348 --> 00:23:04,184
I was a bit late, wasn't I?

220
00:23:30,699 --> 00:23:33,027
It's yours, Choi Choon Hee.

221
00:23:38,725 --> 00:23:40,525
- Over there.
- Joon Hyun!

222
00:23:40,525 --> 00:23:43,155
Joon Hyun!

223
00:23:43,155 --> 00:23:45,524
Goodness, my son!

224
00:23:45,524 --> 00:23:48,767
Son, what happened?
I heard you were in an accident!

225
00:23:48,767 --> 00:23:51,334
- Don't worry, I'm fine.
- Are you really okay?

226
00:23:51,334 --> 00:23:55,982
Yeah. But how did you know
that I was here?

227
00:23:55,982 --> 00:23:57,708
I tried calling and
the nurse picked up.

228
00:23:57,708 --> 00:24:01,581
But Joon Hyun, who were you
in such a rush to see?

229
00:24:01,581 --> 00:24:03,285
Huh?

230
00:24:03,285 --> 00:24:07,036
A friend who lives far away came by
and left without a word.

231
00:24:07,036 --> 00:24:09,259
I went looking for that friend, and...

232
00:24:09,259 --> 00:24:13,125
But now the engagement party is ruined
because of me. What will you do?

233
00:24:13,125 --> 00:24:14,929
Is that the issue right now?

234
00:24:14,942 --> 00:24:16,757
We can reschedule
the engagement party.

235
00:24:16,757 --> 00:24:19,037
You should be getting better right now.

236
00:24:19,037 --> 00:24:21,255
Still, what a relief.

237
00:24:21,255 --> 00:24:26,268
Someone was complaining because they
didn't know you were in an accident...

238
00:24:28,139 --> 00:24:30,751
What a relief. Oh, my son.

239
00:24:30,751 --> 00:24:34,952
In any case, nothing good
can come from Yang Joo Hee's family.

240
00:24:34,952 --> 00:24:38,093
Like that accident on stage
and today's accident, too...

241
00:24:38,093 --> 00:24:40,678
What's going on?

242
00:24:43,322 --> 00:24:46,721
Figures, in Sung Joo's accident too...

243
00:24:48,038 --> 00:24:49,778
There was an accident in the past?

244
00:24:52,020 --> 00:24:54,476
No, my son. It was nothing at all.

245
00:25:13,835 --> 00:25:17,396
Now that our son-in-law is well,
we should continue with the engagement.

246
00:25:17,396 --> 00:25:22,036
You saved me at the concert.
I won't ever forget that.

247
00:25:25,565 --> 00:25:30,914
Even if this gets out, let's take care
of Choi Choon Hee for good next time.

248
00:26:09,716 --> 00:26:11,720
Are you awake now?

249
00:26:15,954 --> 00:26:18,736
You're looking for the man
that came in with you, right?

250
00:26:18,736 --> 00:26:21,192
- Singer Jang Joon Hyun.
- Was he really hurt?

251
00:26:21,192 --> 00:26:23,366
- Did he look okay?
- He went back home earlier.

252
00:26:23,366 --> 00:26:27,391
It's a relief that
both of you are fine.

253
00:26:27,391 --> 00:26:29,473
Ah, yes.

254
00:26:32,974 --> 00:26:35,237
That guy has no loyalty.

255
00:26:35,237 --> 00:26:37,469
How can he just leave?

256
00:26:39,637 --> 00:26:43,275
But it's a relief to
hear that he's fine.

257
00:26:56,098 --> 00:26:58,367
[Missed Call]

258
00:27:08,383 --> 00:27:10,638
You must be giving it
to your girlfriend.

259
00:27:11,812 --> 00:27:14,307
Who is it?

260
00:27:15,714 --> 00:27:17,624
It's President Jo!

261
00:27:22,227 --> 00:27:24,844
Here, a present for the Little Miss.

262
00:27:24,844 --> 00:27:27,504
Wow, it's candy! Looks delicious!

263
00:27:36,526 --> 00:27:38,800
What? You don't like candy?

264
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:40,802
That's not it...

265
00:27:40,802 --> 00:27:43,116
This is a bribe.

266
00:27:43,116 --> 00:27:45,784
- Huh?
- I'm a fair person.

267
00:27:45,784 --> 00:27:48,970
I'm going to keep a firm boundary
with you and Joon Hyun.

268
00:27:48,970 --> 00:27:52,007
I won't stand for it
if you cross it.

269
00:27:52,007 --> 00:27:54,691
Ah, so there was that problem!

270
00:27:54,691 --> 00:27:58,641
That's right. How about this then?

271
00:27:58,641 --> 00:28:02,990
You eat this candy and also
eat the ones from that man!

272
00:28:02,990 --> 00:28:04,959
That's fair then.

273
00:28:04,959 --> 00:28:07,943
It's fair not to receive anything
from anyone

274
00:28:07,943 --> 00:28:10,370
but isn't it also fair to accept
gifts from both people?

275
00:28:10,370 --> 00:28:12,547
- Isn't that right?
- Oh!

276
00:28:12,547 --> 00:28:14,462
All right, here.

277
00:28:19,713 --> 00:28:21,806
What's this?

278
00:28:22,298 --> 00:28:25,163
I have to hand it to these adults.

279
00:28:25,163 --> 00:28:28,229
You shouldn't joke around
with food!

280
00:28:28,229 --> 00:28:29,925
I really thought it was candy!

281
00:28:29,925 --> 00:28:32,513
The real candy's here!

282
00:28:40,205 --> 00:28:41,774
- Is it good?
- Yes.

283
00:28:44,978 --> 00:28:46,863
This is for your sister.
Chocolate.

284
00:28:46,863 --> 00:28:50,976
Wow, chocolate!
I really like chocolate!

285
00:28:50,976 --> 00:28:52,920
No, you can't eat this, Byul.

286
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:55,283
There's a bitter alcohol in here
that only adults can eat.

287
00:28:55,283 --> 00:28:57,645
- Liquor?
- Yeah.

288
00:28:57,645 --> 00:29:00,333
Your sister is probably having
a hard day today.

289
00:29:00,333 --> 00:29:05,285
Tell her to eat these and
have sweet dreams tonight.

290
00:29:05,285 --> 00:29:07,249
Got it?

291
00:29:07,249 --> 00:29:09,858
I think I know what you mean.

292
00:29:19,324 --> 00:29:21,682
What?

293
00:29:21,682 --> 00:29:23,922
This competition has
gone on, but it feels

294
00:29:23,935 --> 00:29:26,186
like the other competitor
has withdrawn.

295
00:29:27,203 --> 00:29:29,254
Jang Joon Hyun didn't get engaged.

296
00:29:29,254 --> 00:29:32,075
- What?
- They're rescheduling it.

297
00:29:32,075 --> 00:29:34,603
In any case...

298
00:29:34,603 --> 00:29:38,448
You should probably
pull it more towards you, huh?

299
00:29:38,448 --> 00:29:44,245
So what I'm thinking, is to give you
a proper chance to act as my father.

300
00:29:44,245 --> 00:29:46,281
Huh?

301
00:29:55,497 --> 00:29:58,350
<i>Ji Sook, I'm sorry.</i>

302
00:29:58,350 --> 00:30:02,421
<i>Because of my momentary passion,
I couldn't look at you.</i>

303
00:30:02,421 --> 00:30:06,054
<i>I'll just keep watch over you
from a distance.</i>

304
00:30:10,722 --> 00:30:11,979
Tae Song!

305
00:30:11,979 --> 00:30:14,617
- Hi, Pil Nyeo.
- Have you been well?

306
00:30:14,617 --> 00:30:17,554
Look how much better you look
after being away for some time.

307
00:30:17,554 --> 00:30:22,063
It must make a difference. I feel
great and my skin feels good, too.

308
00:30:22,063 --> 00:30:26,699
Oh. Then you two went
on a trip together?

309
00:30:26,699 --> 00:30:29,308
So you've officially
become a couple then?

310
00:30:29,308 --> 00:30:31,364
We've officially become a couple!

311
00:30:32,305 --> 00:30:34,750
Ji Sook!

312
00:30:35,979 --> 00:30:39,464
No, it's good.

313
00:30:41,780 --> 00:30:44,211
Let's eat together.
Why are you eating alone?

314
00:30:44,211 --> 00:30:46,448
Should we order one more?

315
00:30:46,448 --> 00:30:49,262
- I'm... done. Done.
- You still have a lot left.

316
00:30:49,262 --> 00:30:51,097
You can't.

317
00:30:51,097 --> 00:30:53,042
- Goodbye.
- I'm leaving!

318
00:30:55,209 --> 00:30:57,381
They're embarrassed.

319
00:31:02,685 --> 00:31:03,961
Hi.

320
00:31:06,045 --> 00:31:08,274
I'm your top fan.

321
00:31:08,274 --> 00:31:12,543
- Hello.
- You're prettiest when you smile

322
00:31:12,543 --> 00:31:17,051
so why does your face look like it's
carrying all the burdens of the world?

323
00:31:20,959 --> 00:31:24,316
Should we hold a fan meeting
to boost your spirits?

324
00:31:24,316 --> 00:31:26,000
- A fan meeting?
- Yes.

325
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:29,135
Hi.

326
00:31:34,168 --> 00:31:37,244
What? Are you worried because
it'll be expensive?

327
00:31:37,244 --> 00:31:39,486
Afraid I might ask you to pay?

328
00:31:39,486 --> 00:31:41,976
Of course not, of course not at all.

329
00:31:41,976 --> 00:31:46,073
I'm just kidding.
Over here.

330
00:31:49,976 --> 00:31:54,100
President Jo.
What are you doing here?

331
00:31:55,718 --> 00:31:58,718
- I planned this with my father.
- Father...

332
00:31:58,718 --> 00:32:01,235
He's your father?

333
00:32:02,668 --> 00:32:04,736
- President Jo Hee Moon...
- Father.

334
00:32:04,736 --> 00:32:06,954
Goodness, oh my!

335
00:32:06,954 --> 00:32:10,321
There were so many things
I was curious about!

336
00:32:10,321 --> 00:32:14,279
I heard that you told Jang Joon Hyun
to train me.

337
00:32:14,279 --> 00:32:16,793
But how did you know who I was?

338
00:32:16,793 --> 00:32:19,365
I was the one who trained your mother.

339
00:32:19,365 --> 00:32:23,068
It was the first job I had
when I established Shine Star.

340
00:32:24,549 --> 00:32:31,549
Then the person who gave up
singing was... my mother?

341
00:32:31,549 --> 00:32:33,117
That's right.

342
00:32:33,117 --> 00:32:37,136
Your mother was a great singer.

343
00:32:40,952 --> 00:32:43,130
But you knew about this too, President?

344
00:32:43,130 --> 00:32:46,678
What? No, I just found out.

345
00:32:46,678 --> 00:32:51,619
But Father, Choon Hee must take after
her mother's excellent singing talent.

346
00:32:51,619 --> 00:32:55,497
That's right. I sometimes
see Choon Hee's

347
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:59,398
mother in Choon Hee's
performances.

348
00:33:00,089 --> 00:33:04,198
How about you make your mother's dreams
come true, Choi Choon Hee?

349
00:33:13,186 --> 00:33:18,918
<i>Mom, I want to become
an impressive singer like you.</i>

350
00:33:21,539 --> 00:33:24,485
<i>You're going to help me
concentrate on singing, right?</i>

351
00:33:27,599 --> 00:33:29,409
<i>I miss you.</i>

352
00:34:03,207 --> 00:34:05,473
Who is it?

353
00:34:06,639 --> 00:34:09,693
Is this Choi Choon Hee's...

354
00:34:12,409 --> 00:34:14,127
Why are you at our house?

355
00:34:15,715 --> 00:34:17,163
Hey, Choi Choon Hee.

356
00:34:18,695 --> 00:34:22,278
Next time that happens,
don't get involved.

357
00:34:22,278 --> 00:34:26,518
If you have to get involved...
then call me.

358
00:34:33,387 --> 00:34:34,763
Boo!

359
00:34:35,377 --> 00:34:37,579
Why I ought to just...

360
00:34:37,579 --> 00:34:39,360
I feel better. Don't
you think of the

361
00:34:39,373 --> 00:34:41,164
person waiting at home
who made you food?

362
00:34:41,164 --> 00:34:44,252
- Hey, I'm sorry.
- Let's go.

363
00:34:44,252 --> 00:34:45,654
Agreed.

364
00:35:14,970 --> 00:35:16,711
What brings you here?

365
00:35:38,214 --> 00:35:41,069
You dropped off my guitar
and left, didn't you?

366
00:35:41,069 --> 00:35:42,495
What was that?

367
00:35:42,495 --> 00:35:45,057
You entrusted that to me
when you were my manager.

368
00:35:45,057 --> 00:35:47,077
I entrusted that to you?

369
00:35:47,077 --> 00:35:49,137
I definitely gave that to the new...

370
00:35:49,137 --> 00:35:51,246
What?

371
00:35:51,246 --> 00:35:53,539
So what I'm saying is that

372
00:35:53,539 --> 00:35:56,521
it's a one of a kind so I wouldn't
have entrusted that to you.

373
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:58,943
I don't know your situation.

374
00:36:00,426 --> 00:36:04,158
Anyhow, what happened
to your engagement party?

375
00:36:04,158 --> 00:36:06,364
We're going to reschedule it.

376
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,003
Good for you.

377
00:36:09,305 --> 00:36:11,527
How could you have run out like that?

378
00:36:11,527 --> 00:36:13,245
What if something even worse happened?

379
00:36:14,468 --> 00:36:16,694
You don't even have a pretty face.

380
00:36:16,694 --> 00:36:19,235
You'll probably look good
if you get a scar.

381
00:36:19,235 --> 00:36:20,376
Did you come all the
way here to say that?

382
00:36:20,389 --> 00:36:21,541
That's not it...

383
00:36:23,380 --> 00:36:25,144
Ah, it's hot!

384
00:36:29,225 --> 00:36:31,157
What's going on?

385
00:36:31,157 --> 00:36:33,955
- Why doesn't the rotation work?
- It's broken.

386
00:36:33,955 --> 00:36:36,316
During the summer?

387
00:36:36,787 --> 00:36:38,974
You're really something.

388
00:36:57,335 --> 00:36:59,513
<i>[Six times for a big one!
four times for a small one!]</i>

389
00:37:13,623 --> 00:37:15,303
I'm leaving.

390
00:37:15,303 --> 00:37:17,441
You called me yesterday, didn't you?

391
00:37:17,441 --> 00:37:20,557
- Yeah.
- How did you know my number?

392
00:37:20,557 --> 00:37:23,036
I asked Tae Song.

393
00:37:24,278 --> 00:37:26,015
Why did you call?

394
00:37:26,015 --> 00:37:28,427
That's because...

395
00:37:29,214 --> 00:37:31,854
I wanted to say thanks.

396
00:37:33,701 --> 00:37:37,858
Thanks... for yesterday.

397
00:37:39,546 --> 00:37:41,653
I'm leaving.

398
00:37:53,716 --> 00:37:56,569
<i>Thanks, Choi Choon Hee.</i>

399
00:37:56,569 --> 00:38:00,886
<i>For saving me... and
for finding my guitar.</i>

400
00:38:06,928 --> 00:38:08,886
What are you talking about?

401
00:38:08,886 --> 00:38:12,892
It's not like we did anything!
Who's Park Soo In to bark out orders?

402
00:38:12,892 --> 00:38:14,866
She wants us to do
a homeless persons' event?

403
00:38:14,866 --> 00:38:16,800
Don't you think it's
too much, Chul Man?

404
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:21,380
Those people don't know
how to be grateful.

405
00:38:21,380 --> 00:38:24,475
Forget all those people
who don't have a conscience!

406
00:38:28,932 --> 00:38:31,609
Choon Hee. What do you think?

407
00:38:33,309 --> 00:38:35,315
I want to do it.

408
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:39,322
I'll think of Dad,
and if he likes my

409
00:38:39,335 --> 00:38:42,468
song, then I think
I'll be strengthened.

410
00:38:42,468 --> 00:38:44,027
Okay, good.

411
00:38:44,027 --> 00:38:47,612
Chul Man, should we do
a dance this time, too?

412
00:38:47,612 --> 00:38:50,748
Of course. How could we not do one?

413
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:57,842
- Isn't that right, Ji Sook?
- You really are amazing, Chul Man.

414
00:38:57,842 --> 00:39:00,682
You're Choon Hee's manager
and her backup dancer.

415
00:39:00,682 --> 00:39:03,287
Do they call that 'a multi-player'?

416
00:39:04,734 --> 00:39:06,231
Goodness, look at me.

417
00:39:08,966 --> 00:39:11,399
Don't worry about the
chorus, Choon Hee.

418
00:39:11,399 --> 00:39:14,361
Tae Song, let's make sure
to practice and get it right this time.

419
00:39:14,361 --> 00:39:15,966
We have to match our lips.

420
00:39:15,966 --> 00:39:17,734
Like this and that,
they have to be in sync...

421
00:39:19,177 --> 00:39:21,286
Oh my endorphins.

422
00:39:21,286 --> 00:39:23,217
Thank you, everyone.

423
00:39:26,194 --> 00:39:27,745
- Tae Song.
- Huh?

424
00:39:31,029 --> 00:39:33,437
Pil Nyeo.

425
00:39:36,715 --> 00:39:37,858
Goodness.

426
00:39:37,858 --> 00:39:40,774
P...Pil Nyeo...

427
00:39:43,946 --> 00:39:46,402
Pil Nyeo! Pil Nyeo!

428
00:39:48,285 --> 00:39:52,140
Good good! Your voice
just came through from behind you.

429
00:39:52,140 --> 00:39:54,488
Now that you have your sound down.

430
00:39:54,488 --> 00:39:58,074
The 'feel' is very important in trot.

431
00:39:58,074 --> 00:39:59,952
'Feel.' Listen.

432
00:40:04,994 --> 00:40:09,280
<i>It was like this from the start.
I liked you</i>

433
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:13,282
<i>from the moment I first met you.</i>

434
00:40:13,282 --> 00:40:20,321
<i>Like a cold, I get feverish
and that's how I knew it was love.</i>

435
00:40:20,321 --> 00:40:23,057
<i>The wind is blowing</i>

436
00:40:23,057 --> 00:40:29,060
<i>on my heart topped with
desert and sand.</i>

437
00:40:29,060 --> 00:40:36,794
<i>As the rain droplets fell,
a flower bloomed.</i>

438
00:40:36,794 --> 00:40:44,545
<i>I want to live happily with you
like a happy pigeon.</i>

439
00:40:44,667 --> 00:40:47,285
- Hello.
- Hello.

440
00:40:48,568 --> 00:40:50,988
I'm trusting you all today!
Let's get together!

441
00:40:50,988 --> 00:40:53,141
We're... we're really doing this, okay?

442
00:40:53,141 --> 00:40:55,751
Let's do our best and be serious.

443
00:40:55,751 --> 00:40:58,887
Start! Choi Choon Hee!
Choi Choon Hee! Fighting!

444
00:40:59,437 --> 00:41:01,439
- Fighting!
- I'm really nervous.

445
00:41:06,721 --> 00:41:08,906
Hello. I'm singer Choi Choon Hee.

446
00:41:08,906 --> 00:41:13,812
I'll be singing 'My Way'
for you all today.

447
00:41:13,812 --> 00:41:17,235
How noisy! It's hard enough
living as  it is!

448
00:41:17,235 --> 00:41:20,935
- We can't even eat in peace?
- That's right! Let us eat!

449
00:41:22,580 --> 00:41:25,785
Mister, you're very tired, aren't you?

450
00:41:25,785 --> 00:41:29,382
I really had a hard time
making a living, too.

451
00:41:29,382 --> 00:41:33,696
But the thing about music...
is that it's a great strength.

452
00:41:33,696 --> 00:41:36,740
So if you give me just three minutes...

453
00:41:36,740 --> 00:41:41,560
I want to be a small source
of strength for you all today.

454
00:41:42,074 --> 00:41:45,563
Could I sing just one song for you?
Thank you.

455
00:41:45,563 --> 00:41:48,474
Then I'll be singing 'My Way' for you!

456
00:42:04,966 --> 00:42:09,687
<i>I thought that I came a long way.</i>

457
00:42:09,687 --> 00:42:13,513
<i>I look back and you aren't there.</i>

458
00:42:13,513 --> 00:42:14,831
<i>- Not there!
- Not there!</i>

459
00:42:14,831 --> 00:42:19,521
<i>I really thought it would
rain hard.</i>

460
00:42:19,521 --> 00:42:23,219
<i>But there wasn't any.</i>

461
00:42:23,219 --> 00:42:24,689
<i>- Wasn't any!
- Wasn't any!</i>

462
00:42:24,689 --> 00:42:29,290
<i>At first I wasn't afraid...</i>

463
00:42:29,290 --> 00:42:34,169
<i>But that scaredy cat changed
after some time.</i>

464
00:42:34,169 --> 00:42:38,259
<i>Everyone can fall at least once.</i>

465
00:42:38,259 --> 00:42:43,387
<i>But you can't get yourself down now.</i>

466
00:42:43,387 --> 00:42:49,071
<i>Until the day I collapse
going down my path</i>

467
00:42:49,071 --> 00:42:53,968
<i>I'm going to stand up and
face it one more time.</i>

468
00:42:53,968 --> 00:42:58,392
<i>Everyone can fall at least once</i>

